Available Data (Feature Explanation)

The dataset contains demographic, academic, and behavioural information about each student:

Student Age: Age group of the student (e.g., 18, 19–22, 23–27).
Sex: Gender of the student.
Graduated High-School Type: Type of high school attended (e.g., State, Private, Other).
Scholarship Type: Percentage of tuition scholarship received (e.g., 50%, 75%, 100%). Higher values may indicate stronger academic performance or financial support.
Additional Work: Whether the student has a job besides studying (Yes/No).
Sports Activity: Participation in sports activities (Yes/No).
Transportation: Main mode of transport to university (Bus or Private).


Academic Behaviour Features
Weekly Study Hours: Number of hours spent studying per week.
Attendance: Class attendance level (Always, Sometimes, Never).
Reading: Whether the student regularly reads course materials (Yes/No).
Notes: Whether the student takes notes during classes (Yes/No).
Listening in Class: Level of attention in class (Yes/No).
Project Work: Participation and engagement in projects (Yes/No).


Target Variable
Grade: Final academic performance category (AA, BA, BB, CC, DD, Fail).



